AGI - The sixth night of the Pope at the Gemini was well spent. This morning Francis rose and had breakfast. To update on the conditions of the Pontiff was the Vatican press room. A new medical bulletin is expected for the late afternoon.&nbsp;
<div </div
<h2> Between today and tomorrow we will understand the reaction to therapy
Today and tomorrow we can better understand the reaction to drug therapy followed by Pope Francis. That's how it learns from Vatican sources. Since yesterday, the medical bulletin issued by the Vatican Press Office underlines a slight improvement in clinical conditions, although the picture remains complex. A decision has not yet been made for the Angelus, Sunday.&nbsp;
Presumably the recitation of the Angelus will take place in the same modalities as last Sunday, that is, the widespread and unread text. Pope Francis continues, although in a reduced form, work. After breakfast, the Pontiff rises and moves in the armchair. His collaborators do the spolade between the Vatican and the Gemelli to take the documents to view or sign.

