AGI - The Faber Village plant on the Lungomare Paolo Toscanelli in Ostia was on fire at night. The Fire Department intervened on the spot and an investigation was opened on the causes of the stake. The establishment for years has been controlled by the Fascian clan,>&nbsp; carried out in 2013, and finished in controlled administration, is now in the hands of the National Agency for the management of goods confiscated from organized crime>.&nbsp; At the moment, the investigations by the competent authorities are under way to clarify the origin of the stake and establish its nature. To give a sign of attention and closeness to citizenship, the City Hall X of Rome Capital suspended the Council today's session > to carry out an inspection on the spot and ensure maximum commitment in the protection of the territory.<br> <br> "We are in constant contact with the forces of the order and with all the competent institutions to make full light on what happened - declared &nbsp;<b>Mario Falconi – At the moment we do not know the origin of the fire, but I want to reassure citizens: the safety of our coastline is an absolute priority > We will always continue to work with determination to protect the community, our promenade and legality, strengthening virtuous paths and sustainable development for our territory. The municipal administration will carefully follow the developments of the investigation and will continue in the commitment to ensure a safer, transparent and accessible coastline for all". &nbsp;
<h2>Forza Italia, rogo does not surprise us
"This night's stake at Faber Village is the eternal wound in the heart of Ostia. The Faber has been a meeting place for years of the Ledense and Roman youth and seeing it today reduced in the degradation and in the incumbent is painful. Unfortunately, we are not surprised: we had put in Capitodoglio a question >representing the concerns of the citizens who live the neighborhood, the promenade, the beach, and who must live every day with a land of nobody, without surveillance, vandalized and shelter for without fixed abode, as reported several times by Forza Italia through our managing Gianni Galatà. So, today's stake is unfortunately a disaster announced.» We ask the competent institutions to secure the area, which is now accessible to all, and to prepare a recovery and relaunch plan." &nbsp; In a note, the Councillors of Forza Italia at Campidoglio > Francesco Carpano and Rachele Mussolini, the CEO of Forza Italia Roma Francesco Bucci and the coordinator of Forza Italia Municipio X Renzo Pallotta.
<br "The causes of the rogue are not yet clear, but we wish the Order's forces good work in carrying out investigations. However, we note that the episode comes close to the competition of the new bathing concessions, > just as it happened last year with the Mecs Village of Capocotta. A disturbing signal that should not be underestimated. We will be on the front line to promote a new season of relaunch of the coast that can only pass for security and legality".
